Given,<br><br>$$f(x) = \left\{ {\matrix{
   {2x + 1,} &amp; { - 3 &lt; x &lt;  - 2}  \cr 
   {x - 1,} &amp; { - 2 \le x &lt; 0}  \cr 
   {x + 2,} &amp; {0 \le x &lt; 1}  \cr 

 } } \right.$$<br><br>Here, $$f( - {2^ - }) = 2( - 2) + 1 =  - 3$$<br><br>$$f( - {2^ + }) =  - 2 - 1 =  - 3$$<br><br>Here, $$f( - {2^ - }) = f( - {2^ + })$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ f(x) is continuous t x = $$-$$2<br><br>and, $$f({0^ - }) = (0 - 1) =  - 1$$<br><br>$$f({0^ + }) = 0 + 2 = 0$$<br><br>Here, $$f({0^ - }) \ne f({0^ + })$$<br><br>$$\therefore$$ f(x) is discontinuous at x = 0<br><br>$$\therefore$$ f(x) is discontinuous at x = 0<br><br>but continuous at every point.

