   {rb} &amp; {pc} &amp; {qa}  \cr 

 } } \right|$$<br><br>On expanding along R<sub>1</sub>, we get<br><br>$$ = pa[{a^2}qr - bc{p^2}] - qb[ca{q^2} - {b^2}pr] + rc[{c^2}pq - ab{r^2}]$$<br><br>$$ = {a^3}pqr - abc{p^3} - abc{q^3} + pqr{b^3} + pqr{c^3} - abc{r^3}$$<br><br>$$ = pqr({a^3} + {b^3} + {c^3}) - abc({p^3} + {q^3} + {r^3})$$<br><br>$$ = pqr(3abc) - abc(3pqr)$$<br><br>[$$\because$$ x + y + z = 0, then x<sup>3</sup> + y<sup>3</sup> + z<sup>3</sup> = 3xyz]<br><br>$$ = 3abcpqr - 3abcpqr = 0$$
